abstract: Agricultural Bank of China, seeking to raise more than $23 billion in the world’s biggest initial public offering, will launch the Shanghai portion of its I.P.O. this week, potentially stretching market liquidity and diverting funds away from rivals, Reuters reported.

lead_paragraph: Agricultural Bank of China, seeking to raise more than $23 billion in the world’s biggest initial public offering, will introduce the Shanghai portion of its I.P.O. this week, potentially stretching market liquidity and diverting funds away from rivals, Reuters reported.

headline.main: AgBank to Introduce Shanghai I.P.O. This Week
